Hi, I am currently migrating a project to Orleans 7 and I have a problem with the TestCluster and NewtonsoftJson/SystemJson serializer. Some of the grains have an external Result class from the nuget package `CSharpFunctionalExtensions` as return type which needs an external Serializer. 

A simple grain which causes the problem:

```csharp
public class HelloWorldGrain : Grain, IHelloWorldGrain
{
    public Task<Result<string>> Hello()
    {
        return Task.FromResult(Result.Success("Hello World"));
    }
}
```

The silo setup looks like this: 

```csharp
IHostBuilder builder = Host.CreateDefaultBuilder(args)
    .UseOrleans(silo =>
    {
        silo.UseLocalhostClustering()
            .ConfigureLogging(logging => logging.AddConsole());

        silo.Services
            .AddAdditionalSerializers();
    })
    .UseConsoleLifetime();
```

The serializer for the `CSharpFunctionalExtensions` namespace is added via an extensions method for `IServiceCollection` which looks like this:
```csharp
    public static IServiceCollection AddAdditionalSerializers(this IServiceCollection serviceCollection)
    {
        serviceCollection
            .AddSerializer(serilzerBuilder =>
                serilzerBuilder.AddNewtonsoftJsonSerializer(isSupported: type =>
                    type.Namespace!.StartsWith("CSharpFunctional")));

        return serviceCollection;
    }
```

It works without a problem when you start the application as a console application but it does not work when starting a `TestCluster` for unittesting. When deploying the TestCluster an `Orleans.Runtime.OrleansConfigurationException` is thrown.

## Sample unit test
```csharp
public class UnitTest1
{
    [Fact]
    public async Task Test1()
    {
        var builder = new TestClusterBuilder();
        builder.AddSiloBuilderConfigurator<TestSiloConfigurations>();
        var cluster = builder.Build();
        await cluster.DeployAsync();

        var factory = cluster.GrainFactory;
        var grain = factory.GetGrain<IHelloWorldGrain>("Grain");

        var result = await grain.Hello();
        result.IsSuccess.Should().BeTrue();
    }
}

public class TestSiloConfigurations : ISiloConfigurator
{
    public void Configure(ISiloBuilder siloBuilder)
    {
        siloBuilder.ConfigureServices(services =>
        {
            services.AddAdditionalSerializers();
        });
    }
}
```

