You can pass a fully qualified class name to `GetGrain()` as optional parameter:
```csharp
GetGrain<IGrainInterface>(key, "your-namespace.B");
GetGrain<IGrainInterface>(key, "your-namespace.C");
```

or just a prefix of the fully qualified name, if the grain classes are defined in different namespaces:
```csharp
GetGrain<IGrainInterface>(key, "B-namespace");
GetGrain<IGrainInterface>(key, "C-namespace");
```
The namespace approach works well for switching between different implementations of multiple grain classes, for example, between test and production.

